I have a Navx-2-MXP v4.3; this is the first time we have used the one with the MXP port plugged into the RoboRio (we have used the smaller USB only ones in the past with no issue). When plugged into MXP, it does not work: does not seem to finish startup calibration (I put a while loop in to wait until isCalibrating is not true to proceed and it never finishes robotInit. The console says the same messages whether or not the Navx is plugged in to MXP:

Instantiating NavX on roboRIO MXP Port. ﻿
﻿﻿﻿﻿﻿﻿ NavX: Library for FRC ﻿
﻿﻿﻿﻿﻿﻿ Failed to allocate DIO 16 ﻿
﻿﻿﻿﻿﻿﻿ NavX: Yaw Reset request ignored - startup calibration is currently in progress.

When I switch it to USB, it works fine, both in Navx UI and in robot code. (on USB, I still get the Yaw Reset Request Ignored because I’m running it right after the constructor, but it eventually gives messages that calibration is complete and auto-reset occurred).

Is there something not connected, not communicating, not enabled? Can’t find anything in documentation or lots of online searching.
